body_html:
Okay, this bug is my mistake, it turns out. It appears I was loading an extra stale copy of a shared object, form what I can tell.

For those curious, I did make a tiny sample project, which helped me realize the issue was certainly on my side. If anyone ends up on this page looking for a how-to on creating a new dataset op, you can check out this repo.

Thanks for the help @mrry!

body:
Okay, this bug is my mistake, it turns out. It appears I was loading an extra stale copy of a shared object, form what I can tell.

For those curious, I did make a tiny sample project, which helped me realize the issue was certainly on my side. If anyone ends up on this page looking for a how-to on creating a new dataset op, you can check out this [repo](https://github.com/galv/tensorflow-dataset-op-lib).

Thanks for the help @mrry!
